body:
If writing directly to the destination, then the table is created on the first write, but only when the first pane actually contains elements that are destined for that table. If the first pane does not contain such elements, the CreateDisposition is currently inadvertently set to CreateNever, which produces production issues for me:
```
java.lang.RuntimeException: Failed to create job with prefix beam_load_iottimeseriesdatapipeline_399f52a8d4c249c387948d3472b516b4_a9bbce63e9d84f698e587084f1402bd1_00001_00345, reached max retries: 1000, last failed job: {
  "configuration" : {
    "jobType" : "LOAD",
    "load" : {
      "clustering" : {
        "fields" : [ "device_id" ]
      },
      "createDisposition" : "CREATE_NEVER",
      "destinationTable" : {
        "datasetId" : "device_metrics_raw",
        "projectId" : "awair-stg",
        "tableId" : "diskused_awairgateway"
      },
      "ignoreUnknownValues" : false,
      "sourceFormat" : "NEWLINE_DELIMITED_JSON",
      "timePartitioning" : {
        "field" : "timestamp",
        "requirePartitionFilter" : true,
        "type" : "DAY"
      },
      "writeDisposition" : "WRITE_APPEND"
    }
  },
```

which shows up despite explicitly setting:
```
.to(
        new BigqueryDestinationFunc(project, datasetName)
      ).withClustering(
      ).optimizedWrites(
      ).withWriteDisposition(
        WriteDisposition.WRITE_APPEND
      ).withCreateDisposition(
        CreateDisposition.CREATE_IF_NEEDED
      ).withMethod(
        BigQueryIO.Write.Method.FILE_LOADS
      ).withTriggeringFrequency(
        Duration.standardMinutes(5)
      )
```
